# --- Finary authentication -------------------------------------------------
# Finary has no official API. This server authenticates the same way the web app
# does: with the long-lived Clerk `__client` cookie, which it uses to mint the
# short-lived tokens each API call needs.
#
# How to get it:
#   1. Log in to https://app.finary.com in your browser.
#   2. Open DevTools → Application (Storage) → Cookies → https://clerk.finary.com
#   3. Copy the VALUE of the `__client` cookie (a long JWT, NOT `__client_uat`).
#   4. Paste it below.
#
# It stays valid for months. If calls start returning 401/"expired", re-copy it.
FINARY_CLERK_CLIENT=

# --- Optional: protect the MCP endpoint ------------------------------------
# When deployed publicly, require HTTP Basic Auth on /mcp. "user:password".
# Leave unset for local dev / private tunnel.
# MCP_BASIC_AUTH=you:some-long-random-password

# --- Optional: pin the account context -------------------------------------
# Auto-derived from your account by default. Only set to override.
# FINARY_ORG_ID=
# FINARY_MEMBERSHIP_ID=
